<h1>The adventures of Commander Nova</h1>

<h2>INCOMING TRANSMISSION — DEEP SPACE DIVISION ARCHIVE<h2>


<p>Commander Nova is the furthest human being from Earth in recorded history.

Assigned to the Outer Reach Surveying Initiative aboard the ISV Meridian Ghost, 
she travels alone through uncharted star systems, cataloguing worlds that no 
human eye has ever seen. Armed with scientific instruments, an AI navigator named 
ARIA, and an unshakeable sense of wonder, Nova documents everything — the 
breathtaking, the strange, and the quietly terrifying.

These are her logs. Transmitted across tens of light-years, delayed by 72 hours, 
and received here at Deep Space Division headquarters for archiving and review.

She is out there right now, somewhere beyond the edge of the map. By the time 
you read this, she is already somewhere new.

*Read her logs. The universe is stranger than you think.*</p>



